Package chess.domain.pieces

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Bishop
    This class corresponds physical bishop-piece thus only containing knowledge of it's place and a method to copy it.
    King
    This class corresponds physical king-piece thus only containing knowledge of it's place and whether or not is has been moved.
    Knight
    This class corresponds physical knight-piece thus only containing knowledge of it's place and a method to copy it.
    Pawn
    This class corresponds physical bishop-piece thus only containing knowledge of it's place, whether or not is has moved yet and if it moved two squares last turn.
    Piece
    This is an abstract parent class of all chess pieces containing information of its location and owner.
    Queen
    This class corresponds physical queen-piece thus only containing knowledge of it's place and a method to copy it.
    Rook
    This class corresponds physical rook-piece thus only containing knowledge of it's place and whether or not it has been moved so far.
